 an atmosphere of apparent compliance. Working the System will appeal to anthropologists and political scientists, urban sociologists, and scholars of African studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEthnologyzAngola. 0aPolitics and culturezAngola. 0aPostwar reconstructionxSocial aspectszAngola. 0aPower (Social sciences)zAngola. 4aAfrican Hist & Diaspora. 4aAnthropology. 4aLabor History.  aneo-authoritarian regimes, New Angola, contemporary Angolan polity, political transformation in Angola, the dynamics of a petro-state, political history of Angola.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501709692?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709692423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501709692/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles